:: StoryTitle
Subtext Demo

:: StorySubtitle
an interactive chat story

:: Story JavaScript [script]

var menuContent = '<h3>Welcome</h3><p>Thanks for trying out <a href="https://github.com/samplereality/subtext">Subtext</a>.</p><p>Anything passed to <span style="font-family: monospace;">story.setMenu()</span> in your Story JavaScript appears here.</p>';

story.setMenu(menuContent);
story.config.hint = 'Choose an option to continue the conversation';

// different helper text above the free-text composer, and stop
// showing hints once the player has made a few moves
story.config.inputHint = 'Type your reply to continue';
story.config.hintFadeAfter = 4;

story.config.sounds = true;

// narrator (speakerless) passages float over the blurred chat;
// other options: 'chat' (inside the conversation) or 'notification'
// (a phone-style banner) — or per passage via the tags
// meta-chat / meta-overlay / meta-notification
story.config.metaStyle = 'overlay';


:: StorySpeakers
1: Alex; color: #5e5ce6
2: Sam; avatar: data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' viewBox='0 0 100 100'%3E%3Crect width='100' height='100' fill='%23148F77'/%3E%3Ccircle cx='50' cy='38' r='16' fill='%23F9E79F'/%3E%3Cpath d='M20 92c0-20 13-30 30-30s30 10 30 30z' fill='%23F9E79F'/%3E%3C/svg%3E


:: Start [speaker-1]
[timestamp Today 9:41 AM]

hi!

👋

[[hello]]
[[whatsup?!]]


:: hello
A passage without a speaker tag belongs to the narrator.

This story shows narration as an overlay above the chat — it can also sit inside the conversation, or arrive as a phone notification.

[[ok]]

:: ok [speaker-2]
<%= either('how are you doing?', 'how are things on your end?', 'how goes it?') %>

[[pretty good]]
[[not so well]]
[[timeout:20 um… good, I guess?->pretty good]]


:: whatsup?! [speaker-2]
all good in the hood...

each paragraph of a passage becomes its own message bubble

which makes longer passages feel like a real text exchange 💬

[[where are you from?]]
[[what is your name?]]


:: pretty good [speaker-1]
nice to hear!

what's the weather like where you are? send me a photo ☀️

[[photo:*->photo-reply]]
[[rather not say->Start]]

:: photo-reply [speaker-1]
<% if (s.lastPhoto === 'sunny') { %>gorgeous! enjoy the sunshine 😎<% } else { %>oh no, stay dry out there ☔<% } %>

you've sent me <%= s.sentPhotos.length %> photo(s) so far

[[start over?->Start]]

